{"id":4552,"date":"2023-12-08T15:46:03","date_gmt":"2023-12-08T04:46:03","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/?post_type=help_centre&#038;p=4552"},"modified":"2023-12-08T15:49:03","modified_gmt":"2023-12-08T04:49:03","slug":"main-drive-unit-slides-up-and-down-the-mast","status":"publish","type":"help_centre","link":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/help-centre\/troubleshooting\/main-drive-unit-slides-up-and-down-the-mast\/","title":{"rendered":"Main drive unit slides up and down the mast"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>The solution involves adjusting the inserts if you encounter an issue with the main drive unit sliding up and down the mast. Follow these steps for a more secure fit:<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><strong>Start with Orange Pads<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Begin by using the orange pads, as they are a versatile choice that fits most mast sizes. Position the main drive unit about 12-15cm from the top of the mast.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"2\"><li><strong>Assess Fitment<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Check the stability of the main drive unit with the orange pads. If the fit is not secure or has excessive sliding, it&#8217;s time to consider alternative inserts.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"3\"><li><strong>Switch to Blue Pads for Extra Thickness<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>If the orange pads are too small and the unit still slides, switch to the thicker blue pads. These pads provide additional thickness, helping to create a snug fit on the mast.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"4\"><li><strong>Consider Grey Pads for a Thinner Option<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>On the other hand, if you find it challenging to tighten the unit enough with the orange or blue pads, try the thinner grey pads. These pads can offer a more precise adjustment for a secure fit.<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"5\"><li><strong>Mix and Match for Optimal Fit<\/strong><\/li><\/ol><p>Experiment with different combinations of pads to achieve the perfect fit. Mixing and matching, such as using grey pads in the front and orange in the back, allows for a customised configuration based on the specific requirements of your mast.<\/p><p>Adjusting the inserts can address the main drive unit sliding issue and achieve a more secure and stable connection on the mast. This flexibility in insert options ensures that the Stoke Foil is adaptable to various mast sizes and allows users to fine-tune the setup for optimal performance.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The solution involves adjusting the inserts if you encounter an issue with the main drive unit sliding up and down the mast. Follow these steps for a more secure fit: Begin by using the orange pads, as they are a versatile choice that fits most mast sizes. Position the main drive unit about 12-15cm from [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"template":"","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"rank_math_lock_modified_date":false,"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-4552","help_centre","type-help_centre","status-publish","hentry","help_centre_category-troubleshooting"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/help_centre\/4552","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/help_centre"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/help_centre"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/help_centre\/4552\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":4554,"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/help_centre\/4552\/revisions\/4554"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=4552"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}